Directions:

If statements allow a computer to execute code when only a conditional evaluates to True. The basic structure of an if statement is as follows

if(condition) :
	# This code runs if condition is True
else:
	# This code runs if conditions is False

Directions:

There are also if-else statements (elif). The if-else statements are used to check multiple conditions in a sequence. The structure is as follows

if(conditionOne):
	# This code runs if conditionOne is True
elif(conditionTwo):
	# This code runs if conditionOne is False and conditionTwo is True
else:
	# This code runs if conditionOne and conditionTwo are False
